Megaports_Program_@PROG Operational in MexicoJuly 26, 2012A U.S. program to deploy radiation_detectors_@WEA at key shipping hubs around the world is now up and running in neighboring Mexico, the Spanish_news_agency_EFE_@ORG reported on Wednesday (see GSN , Oct. 5, 2011).The National_Nuclear_Security_Administration_@ORG's_@REL Megaports_Initiative_@PROG, which is_aimed_at_detecting_the_illicit_shipment_of_@REL potential_nuclear_and_radiological_weapons_materials_@WEA, is now active at Mexico's four chief seaports, according to a press release from the U.S._Embassy_@ORG in the Mexican capital.Both stationary and movable radiation_monitors_@WEA have been put in place at ports in Altamira, Lazaro Cardenas, Manzanillo and Veracruz.
